-- Alleghany Hires Ex-Allied World Manager Sennott as Finance Chief
-- B y   N o a h   B u h a y a r
-- 2013-04-15T21:11:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-15/alleghany-hires-ex-allied-world-manager-sennott-as-finance-chief.html
Alleghany Corp. (Y)  the insurer that
acquired Transatlantic Holdings Inc., said John Sennott has been
hired as chief financial officer, replacing Roger Gorham, who
will oversee the company’s fixed-income portfolio.  Sennott, 47, is former executive vice president and chief
corporate strategy officer at Allied World Assurance Company
Holdings AG, according to a regulatory filing today from New
York-based Alleghany. Gorham’s new duty was announced in
January.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Noah Buhayar in  New York  at 
